 <text>
  <front>
   <head>Anthem for Doomed Youth</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="sonnet">
     <l n="1" met="-+-+-+-+-+-">What passing-bells for these who die as cattle?</l>
     <l n="2" met="+--+-+-+-+">Only the monstrous anger of the guns.</l>
     <l n="3" met="+--+--+-+-+-">Only the stuttering rifles' rapid rattle</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+-+-+-+-+">Can patter out their hasty orisons.</l>
     <l n="5" met="-+--+-+-+-+|++--+-+++-+">No mockeries now for them; no prayers nor bells;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+-+-+-+-+-">Nor any voice of mourning save the choirs,--</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+-+-+--+-+">The shrill, demented choirs of wailing shells;</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+-+-+--++-">And bugles calling for them from sad shires.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="sonnet">
     <l n="9" met="-+-+-+-+-+|++---+-+-+">What candles may be held to speed them all?</l>
     <l n="10" met="+--+-+-+-+">Not in the hands of boys but in their eyes</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+-+-+-+-+">Shall shine the holy glimmers of goodbyes.</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+--++-+-+">The pallor of girls' brows shall be their pall;</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+--+-+-+-+">Their flowers the tenderness of patient minds,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+++-+-+-+">And each slow dusk a drawing-down of blinds.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
